        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Avoid unnecessary logging work",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Avoid evaluating filtered log messages before the active log level check.\n- Skip file-log timestamp, metadata formatting, and redaction work while file logging is disabled.\n- Add a cheap redaction preflight so ordinary log lines avoid regex passes.\n- Add focused regression tests for the logging performance paths.\n\n## Verification\n- `swift test --filter CodexBarLoggingPerformanceTests`\n- `swiftlint --strict Sources/CodexBarCore/Logging/LogRedactor.swift TestsLinux/CodexBarLoggingPerformanceTests.swift`\n- `swift build --build-tests`\n- `swiftlint --strict`\n\n## Behavior Proof\nFocused logging proof rerun locally on June 16, 2026 PT:\n\n```text\n$ swift test --filter CodexBarLoggingPerformanceTests\nBuild complete! (98.09 sec)\nTest run started.\nTesting Library Version: 2067.1\nTarget Platform: arm64e-apple-macos14.0\nSuite CodexBarLoggingPerformanceTests started.\nTest \"filtered log messages are not evaluated\" started.\nTest \"filtered log messages are not evaluated\" passed after 0.001 seconds.\nTest \"disabled file logging does not format metadata\" started.\nTest \"disabled file logging does not format metadata\" passed after 0.001 seconds.\nTest \"redactor leaves ordinary log lines unchanged\" started.\nTest \"redactor leaves ordinary log lines unchanged\" passed after 0.001 seconds.\nTest \"redactor still redacts sensitive log lines\" started.\nTest \"redactor still redacts sensitive log lines\" passed after 0.001 seconds.\nSuite CodexBarLoggingPerformanceTests passed after 0.003 seconds.\nTest run with 4 tests in 1 suite passed after 0.003 seconds.\n```\n\n## Notes\n- Sparkle was already present in `.build/out/Products/Debug/Sparkle.framework`; local test execution needed `.build/out/Products/Debug/PackageFrameworks/Sparkle.framework` to point at it so SwiftPM could load the app test bundle.\n",
